 that's fine. It doesn’t cover line numbers, though.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating the coverage tool**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the coverage tool and how it relies on generated metadata, which means counters aren't really important—it's the behavior that matters more precisely. I plan to read the XercesDOMAdapter source since it likely uses the same parser with the namespace set to true. It looks like the counter assertion in XML4J might reset, so I need to add static counts to improve accuracy. Let's see how it all ties together!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_k3fjj5aBnuZ1Q0RFbDe80Rm3|fc_04d3a5750ac2288e0169fc84fe06cc8197aab0e7390263cebe", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge5/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/jdom/jdom/1.0b8/main/extracted/jdom-b8/src/java/org/jdom/adapters/XercesDOMAdapter.java", "limit": 160}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 875, "output": 1163, "cacheRead": 52736, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54774, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778156777776, "responseId": "resp_04d3a5750ac2288e0169fc84eb1304819789d09f98cb1d9da2"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_k3fjj5aBnuZ1Q0RFbDe80Rm3|fc_04d3a5750ac2288e0169fc84fe06cc8197aab0e7390263cebe", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*-- \r\n\r\n $Id: XercesDOMAdapter.java,v 1.10 2002/01/08 09:17:10 jhunter Exp $\r\n\r\n Copyright (C) 2000 Brett McLaughlin & Jason Hunter.\r\n All rights reserved.\r\n \r\n Redistribution and use in source and binary forms, with or without\r\n modification, are permitted provided that the following conditions\r\n are met:\r\n \r\n 1. Redistributions of source code must retain the above copyright\r\n    notice, this list of conditions, and the following disclaimer.\r\n \r\n 2. Redistributions i